      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are going through this overwhelming loss; it sounds like you are carrying a very heavy burden right now. Please know that while the situation feels like a wall, there are always ways to navigate through it, even if they feel impossible in the moment. You are not alone in this, and reaching out to a trusted friend, family member, or a mental health professional can provide support when you feel stuck.\n\nIf you are feeling like you might hurt yourself or that the pain is too much to bear, please consider reaching out to a crisis line immediately. In the US, you can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or dial 911 for emergency help. These services are there to listen without judgment and guide you toward resources that can help you find a way forward.\n\nYou have survived 100% of your bad days so far, and this difficult week is just one chapter in a much larger story. Even if it feels like everything is gone, there is still hope for rebuilding, and sometimes the first step is just taking a deep breath and acknowledging that you don't have to carry this alone.",
